════════════════════════════════════════════════════
RULES
════════════════════════════════════════════════════

1. NEVER use px for font-size in responsive rules.
   Always use clamp() or rem so text scales with
   user browser preferences.

2. overflow-x: hidden goes on html AND body — not
   just body. Safari needs it on html to work.

3. The Mammut card animation (translateX 110vw) is
   DISABLED below 768px — cards just sit at
   translateX(0). Horizontal animations on mobile
   cause scroll jank and accessibility issues.

4. Ecosystem grid breakpoints:
   1441px+  → 6 columns (desktop)
   1025–1280 → 6 columns, reduced padding
   769–1024 → 3 columns
   481–768  → 2 columns
   0–480    → 1 column
   Never go below 1 column.

5. Use attribute selectors [class*="..."] for 
   journey/persona page selectors where exact 
   class names are unknown. These are broad 
   enough to catch whatever class names exist.

6. min-height: 44px on touch targets is Apple's
   Human Interface Guidelines minimum. Do not
   reduce below this on mobile.

7. Do NOT add !important anywhere except the
   card-wrap transform override on mobile
   (required to override inline style set by JS).

8. Test each breakpoint by resizing the browser
   window — do not assume a breakpoint works
   without checking it visually.

