**The two most important fixes in this prompt:**

**Card animation disable on mobile** — `transform: translateX(110vw)` on mobile creates a 110vw-wide invisible element that the browser thinks is part of the page. Even with `overflow-x: hidden` on the parent, this causes scroll jank and sometimes breaks touch scrolling entirely. Disabling the animation below 768px and just showing cards at position 0 is the right call.

**Ecosystem grid** — the 6-column grid is the hardest to make responsive. The key is `align-items: start` on the grid — without it, all columns stretch to the height of the tallest column (Recruit with 14 items), leaving massive empty space under shorter columns on tablet and mobile.
